Defendant Timothy David Peterson in court.  Attorney Marcus Lasalle Falk in court for Timothy David Peterson.  Attorney Anthony A. Lambrecht in court for State of Wisconsin. 
NO CONTEST to the charge in count 2, possess fentanyl with intent as repeater.  Convicted 
State moves to dismiss and read in counts 1 and 3-5.  Motion granted. 
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of eight (8) years. That's three (3) years initial confinement followed by five (5) years extended supervision.   This sentence to run concurrent with any sentence presently being served.   
Conditions of Extended Supervision: 
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Maintain absolute sobriety;
4) Provide DNA sample
5) Pay court costs;
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
Defendant is found not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program but he is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.
Defendant has credit for 185 days.
